HEADWORD: Redhibition
<hw>Red`hi*bi"tion</hw> <pr>(r?d`h?*b?sh"?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>redhibitio</ets> a taking back.]</ety> <fld>(Civil
Law)</fld> <def>The annulling of a sale, and the return by the buyer of
the article sold, on account of some defect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redhibitory</ent>⟦br⟧
